parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the timing chain can cause the engine to stall or seize, leading to a loss of control and potentially causing accidents. It can also lead to costly repairs and engine damage.
symptoms: Rattling or knocking noise from the engine
oil dipstick not returning to its normal position.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the oil system can cause engine damage, leading to costly repairs and potentially causing accidents.
The failure of the water pump can cause engine overheating, leading to costly repairs and potentially causing accidents.

The faulty passenger seat airbag sensor can cause the airbag warning light to remain on, indicating that the passenger airbag is off, even when the seat is occupied. This can lead to a failure of the airbag to deploy in the event of an accident, potentially resulting in serious injury or death.
symptoms: The airbag warning light remains on
the passenger airbag is indicated as "off" even when the seat is occupied
the seat belt and airbag lights come on intermittently or stay on
the sensor on the passenger seat appears faulty.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause a range of problems, including electrical fires, loss of control, and poor performance, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
Water leaks and water damage can cause electrical failures, corrosion, and damage to circuit boards, which can lead to electrical fires, loss of control, and poor performance.
Faulty outlets and electrical accessories can cause electrical shorts, fires, and other electrical problems, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
